General Info

This LoRA has been trained using the Anything v4.5 model. It does a relatively good job at generating characters that look like Aida Surugan from the Gundam Reconguista in G series. It seems to be rather easy to put her into different clothes and settings using this LoRA as it has very been trained on her face very exactly. Usage

The model has been trained using Kohya so you probably want to use it in the same way as you use other Kohya models. If you are Using A1111's Webui you want to move the file into the models>Lora directory. It is very important to use the relevant trigger word so that you can get results that look close to mine or even better.

items.name: Dino's RichStyle 1.5
items.description:
Dicuki RichStyle

Model trained in SD 1.5 with photos generated with Midjourney, created to generate dinos

You can also make objects... landscapes, etc, but maybe you need more tries:

  • 30 steps - 7cfg

  • euler a,ddim, dpm++sde...

  • you can use different resolutions, you can generate interesting things

  • (portraits 512x616 works nice)

TOKEN: dicuki, dicuki style, dicuki as a "x", dicuki mix "x"

Possible positives: beautiful, cute , 4k, detailed , digital art, trending arstation, film still "x", cinematic, intricate details, disney , pixar

Possible negatives: umbrella, ugly, pencil draw, bad photo, cartoon, bad colors, bad taste, sketch, illustration, low resolution, low quality, cropped, wrong, black and white, bw, out of focus, blurry

You can see the prompts in the images.

Improve images and increase resolution

  • Generate images and choose the one you like the most, and send it to the img2img section.

  • In img2img, choose to generate 2-4 or more images. If you want it to resemble the original photo, set "denoising" to 0.4-0.5-0.6. If you want more changes in the image, you can set "denoising" from 0.6 to 1.

  • Once those 4 images are generated, choose the one you like the most (or generate more images until you find the one you like) and send it back to img2img.

  • Now we will increase the resolution of the image. If the photo is 512x512, we can set it to 680x680 and 50 steps for example (changing "denoising" if we want it to resemble more or less) and generate 2-4 more images again and choose the one we like and send it back to img2img and keep increasing the resolution of the image little by little until you want to, in order to not lose details.

  • At this point, we can lower denoising to 0.15 if we don't want the image to change, and generate 1 image with 50/100 steps, this way we can make giant images with high resolution/quality.

ENJOY !!!!

If you want to share the images, you can tag me on social media or in the comments! I'd LOVE to SEE what you can do with the model!

items.name: 1930's Cartoon RichStyle 1.5
items.description:
1930's Cartoon

Model trained in SD 1.5 with photos generated with Midjourney, created to generate cartoons of 1920-1930's

You can also make objects... landscapes, etc, but maybe you need more tries:

  • 30 steps - 7 and 8.5 cfg

  • euler a,ddim, dpm++sde...

  • you can use different resolutions, you can generate interesting things

  • (portraits 512x616 works nice)

TOKEN: ocds, ocds portrait, ocds style, black and white ocds of...

Possible positives: fleischer studios, high detailed, 4k, grainy

Possible negatives: distorted, bad detail, professional photo, low detail, pencil draw, hat, cap...animal...

You can see the prompts in the images.

Improve images and increase resolution

  • Generate images and choose the one you like the most, and send it to the img2img section.

  • In img2img, choose to generate 2-4 or more images. If you want it to resemble the original photo, set "denoising" to 0.4-0.5-0.6. If you want more changes in the image, you can set "denoising" from 0.6 to 1.

  • Once those 4 images are generated, choose the one you like the most (or generate more images until you find the one you like) and send it back to img2img.

  • Now we will increase the resolution of the image. If the photo is 512x512, we can set it to 680x680 and 50 steps for example (changing "denoising" if we want it to resemble more or less) and generate 2-4 more images again and choose the one we like and send it back to img2img and keep increasing the resolution of the image little by little until you want to, in order to not lose details.

  • At this point, we can lower denoising to 0.15 if we don't want the image to change, and generate 1 image with 50/100 steps, this way we can make giant images with high resolution/quality.

ENJOY !!!!

If you want to share the images, you can tag me on social media or in the comments! I'd LOVE to SEE what you can do with the model!

items.name: Ebo-Nyakim
items.description:
This LORA was trained on Nyakim Gatwech, a model of South Sudanese ancestry. I choose her for her very dark complexion which has better chance of forcing prompts to create dark skin women. Her dataset was trained with the realisticVisionV13 checkpoint.

To test ideal weights, I have generated some images using different checkpoints. The following weights gave better results. With the lower ends being lighter and the higher ends giving more accurate skin tones:

  • Realistic Vision V1.3: 0.6 - 1.2

  • Perfect World: 1.2 - 1.6

  • AnimeIllustDiffusion: 1.6 - 2 (Not very successful)

  • AbyssOrangeMix3: 1.6 - 2

  • Beauty 2.5D: 1.8 - 2 (Favorite)

  • 7th Heaven: 1.2 - 1.6

  • dalcefo painting: 1.4 - 1.8

  • Protogen v2.2 (Anime): 0.8 - 1.2

  • Deliberate: 0.6 - 1.2

  • Liberty: 0.6 - 1

  • ChilloutMix: 0.8 - 1.2 (Afro-Asian)

  • Dreamlike Diffusion: 0.4 - 1 (Afro-Asian)

All tests had the following prompt: <lora:Nyakim:X> Nyakim with long straight hair and blue eyes and green eyeshadow makeup, she is wearing a warm pink flower dress, there is yellow diffuse light reflecting on her skin

items.name: Height Maps
items.description:
I have trained this model with 150 height maps. The training data had a resolution of 768 x 768 pixels to increase the detail of the model.

SD 1.5 was the base and some tags that can be used are:
desert, mountain, mesa, canyon, moon, crater, ocean, single mountain, dunes, islands, lake, river, (large scale, mesa, rocky, lake with mountain).

The results tend to be somewhat random and are occasionally a mix of the desired prompt and another. To prevent this, use some of the above tags as negative prompts.

I would recommend upscaling the image using software of your choice.
I like to use ChainNer and scale the images to 8k, import them into Photoshop, set the bit depth to 16 bit, and set the image size back to 4k. This way you get a good mix of bit depth and resolution.
I haven't found the best model for upscaling, but universal models tend to do a decent job, and models for banding can be used to make the transition smoother

items.name: 17 characters from (mostly) old soviet cartoons + Tom and Jerry
items.description:
This model is trained on the main characters from such cartoons as:

  • Tom and Jerry (Tom the cat and Jerry the mouse)

  • "Nu, pogodi! (wolf and hare)

  • "Masha and the Bear" (Masha and Bear)

  • "Leopold the cat (Leopold the cat, thin white mouse and fat grey mouse)

  • "The kid and Karlsson" (Kid, Karlsson and freken Bok)

  • "Winnie the Pooh" (Winnie the Pooh and Piglet)

  • "Gena the crocodile and Cheburashka" (Gena the crocodile, Cheburashka, Shapokliak the old lady)

Trained on about 30-70 characters of each hero, for about 100 epochs (10 epochs * 10 repeats).

I dont remember all the tokens I assigned to each cartoon hero, but it will be quite easy to understand it by yourself just trying each token one by one.
The model was trained without regularization images, so it forgot all the knowledge it has as SD1.5 model and is able to generate only these 17 characters and their mixes.

I am interested in training cartoon models and creating animations from them, I have about 50+ such models trained, you can see my works with these kind of models at my Youtube channel - https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCIUGlTzaOOc6eOPmQuj1usg

items.name: Red Skin | Feature
items.description:
Training on "red skin".

I have been working to integrate various unique features into LoRa's (and now LoCon). I have found making individual trainings on each feature, then merging the ones needed together gets remarkable results.

This has been trained on about 30 AI generated images from various models (picked out from hundreds), after using a LoRa made on about 1700 images of characters with red skin. This helped to eliminate the style bias and focus on just the feature (in this case red skin).

This can be used stand-alone to add red skin with much higher efficiency, or mixed with other LoRA / LoCon to mix the feature in. I recommend to avoid using this with multiple other LoRA / LoCon without mixing first, it is more prone to cause issues.

If you like this, get me a coffee :D

items.name: Groo the Wanderer
items.description:
This is a dreambooth trained on the comic book character Groo the Wanderer.

The base stable diffusion models struggle to draw this character, my guess that it's because of its unusual style, and insufficient images of him outside of comic book pages, where he appears small and hard to extract from the background.


The trained data is available for download

Version 1 is trained on sd 1.5, with 10 images of Groo with the background removed. it worked better to create funny versions of Groo as a real-life person

Version 2 is trained on sd 2.1 with the same 10 images plus 19 images without their background removed. I didn't upload it as a new version because it got worse at drawing a recognizable Groo if I ask for photorealism, but some things it does better. It makes a much more realistic barbarian

There is a LoRA, that makes more sense for a single character, but I couldn't get the same funny real life version of Groo with that too. It's the same training data as groo-01.

Example images have a different hash because that was before I converted the model to safetensor

items.name: Husbando LoCon
items.description:
You can support me on Ko-fi ☕ if you like my work.

Husbando LoCon is able to generate explicit homoerotic hentai illustrations and illustrations of sexually suggestive males.

Husbando LoCon is the successor of my previous work Husbando LoRA.

Features

  • Easy to generate good-looking masculine characters using Danbooru tags.

  • Good male genitalia.

  • Good solo / solo focus homoerotic content.

  • Homoerotic contents depicting 2 or more people are highly erroneous. You'll need luck and careful prompting to get things right.

Weight Guide

  • For general purpose: 0.5 - 0.6. You can also use a lower weight such as 0.3 if you just want to enhance the sexiness of your character.

  • For explicit art: Set the text encoder weight to 1.0 and U-Net weight to 0.5 - 0.6 with Additional Networks extension. (You need to toggle the "Separate UNet/Text Encoder weights" checkbox.)

How to use

  • Select any checkpoint that works with Danbooru tags. Recommended models: AnyLoRA or AOM series.

  • Select a VAE if the checkpoint model you're using doesn't have a baked-in VAE, or else you'll find your generated images have dull colors. Recommended VAEs: vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned or kl-f8-anime2.

  • Make sure to follow the steps in How to use a LoCon. I suggest you start by setting the weight to 0.5.

  • Generate at 512 base resolution and use hires fix to improve the details. Recommended upscaler: R-ESRGAN 4x+ Anime6B; denoising strength: 0.5.
